    Custom Fusion360 -> URDF -> MJCF humanoid (real-robot deployment track).
    Units: meters (meshes scaled mm->m via scale="0.001"). Total mass ~1.30 kg.
    Structure: free-floating base_link (pelvis) + 17 actuated hinge joints = 18 bodies.
      Right leg : Revolute 18 (hip-roll) -> 26 (hip-yaw) -> 23 (hip-pitch) -> 21 (knee)
      Left  leg : Revolute 24 (hip-roll) -> 28 (hip-yaw) -> 25 (hip-pitch) -> 27 (knee)
      Waist     : Revolute 22 (roll) -> 20 (pitch) -> 19 (yaw)  [carries both arms]
      Left  arm : Revolute 2 -> 6 -> 1 (elbow)
      Right arm : Revolute 4 -> 5 -> 3 (elbow)
    Servo housings / brackets are rigid geoms on their parent link (only the horn
    rotates -> the child body). Validate with scripts/test_model_integrity.py.
    Post-conversion fixes: detailed meshes are visual-only, each link has a simple
    collision BOX (class="col"), self-collision ON with designed overlaps excluded
    (see <contact>), inertials re-grounded in mesh geometry, balanceinertia removed.
  -->
